# Sharpee Multiuser Server — Docker build context filter.
#
# The build context is the repo root (tools/zifmia/Dockerfile reaches
# into packages/* via the workspace). This file keeps the context
# minimal: only the trees the Dockerfile COPYs are shipped to the
# daemon.
#
# Pattern: ignore everything, then re-include packages/ and the
# relevant tools/ subtrees, then prune dev/build artifacts inside.

# Ignore everything by default.
**

# Re-include workspace manifests + root package + root tsconfigs.
!package.json
!pnpm-workspace.yaml
!pnpm-lock.yaml
!tsconfig.json
!tsconfig.base.json
!tsconfig.base-esm.json
!tsconfig.package.json
!tsconfig.dev.json
!turbo.json
!ts-forge.config.json

!packages
!packages/**

!tools
!tools/zifmia
!tools/zifmia/**

# Prune dev/build artifacts inside the included trees.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/dist-cjs
**/dist-npm
**/coverage
**/.turbo
**/.next
**/*.log
**/.DS_Store
**/.git
**/.env
**/.env.*

# Re-include packages' pre-built dist trees (required at runtime — `pnpm
# deploy --prod` materialises them into the runtime image, and Node ESM
# resolution after ADR-162 reaches into dist/ for @sharpee/world-model).
!packages/*/dist
!packages/*/dist/**
!packages/*/dist-esm
!packages/*/dist-esm/**
